The paper discusses a central challenge in data mining, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic programming (cs.LG). The specific focus on itemset, sequence, and graph mining suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The mention of scalability and generic mining systems suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
